Program: Outlook
Title: 31/01/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00n3tb0
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 1 Feb 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the story of Gary Mulgrew, one of the 'Nat West Three' - the British bankers who were controversially extradited to the USA after the collapse of the giant Enron Corporation. Gary tells Matthew Bannister about his rise from a Glasgow children's home to the top of the banking world, about the months he spent in a prison in Texas, and about his ongoing search for his daughter. He's written a book about his experiences called Gang of One. Show less